y = Republican Party (United States)\n|candidate = Jimmy Blake\n|votes = 15,385\n|percentage = 7.06\n}}\n\n{{Election box candidate no party link no change\n|party = Republican Party (United States)\n|candidate = Albert Lipscomb\n|votes = 7,672\n|percentage = 3.52\n}}\n\n{{Election box end}}\n\n{{Election box begin no change|title=1996 Alabama U.S. Senate Republican primary runoff election}}\n\n{{Election box winning candidate with party link no change\n|party = Republican Party (United States)\n|candidate = Jeff Sessions\n|votes = 681\n|percentage = 59.26\n}}\n\n{{Election box candidate no party link no change\n|party = Republican Party (United States)\n|candidate = Sid McDonald\n|votes = 56,156\n|percentage = 40.74\n}}\n\n{{Election box end}}\n\n{{Election box begin no change|title=[[1996 United States Senate election in Alabama]]}}\n{{Election box winning candidate with party link no change|\n  |party      = Republican Party (United States)\n  |candidate  = Jeff Sessions\n  |votes      = 786,436\n  |percentage = 52.45\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link no change|\n  |party      = Democratic Party (United States)\n  |candidate  = Roger Bedford\n  |votes      = 681,651\n  |percentage = 45.46\n}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link no change|\n  |party      = Libertarian Party (United States)\n  |candidate  = Mark Thornton\n  |votes      = 21,550\n  |percentage = 1.44\n}}\n{{Election box candidate no change|\n  |party      = [[Natural Law Party#United States|Natural Law]]\n  |candidate  = Charles R. Hebner\n  |votes      = 9,123\n  |percentage = 0.61\n}}\n{{Election box write-in with party link no change|\n  |votes      = 633\n  |percentage = 0.04\n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n\n;1994\n{{Election box begin no change|title=1994 Alabama Attorney General election}}\n\n{{Election box winning candidate with party link no change\n|party = Republican Party (United States)\n|candidate = Jeff Sessions\n|votes = 667,010\n|percentage = 56.87\n}}\n\n{{Election box candidate with party link no change\n|party = Democratic Party (United States)\n|candidate = Jimmy Evans (incumbent)\n|votes = 505,137\n|percentage = 43.07\n}}\n\n{{Election box write-in with party link no change\n|votes = 660\n|percentage = 0.00\n}}\n\n{{Election box end}}\n\n== See also ==\n* [[2017 dismissal of U.S. attorneys]]\n*''[[Mueller Report]]''\n* [[Nobody Is Above the Law]]\n*[[Timeline of Russian interference in the 2016 United States elections]]\n*[[Timeline of Russian interference in the 2016 United States elections (July 2016 \u2013 election day)]]\n*[[Timeline of post-election transition following Russian interference in the 2016 United States elections]]\n*[[Timeline of investigations into Trump and Russia (January\u2013June 2017)]]\n*[[Timeline of investigations into Trump and Russia (July\u2013December 2017)]]\n*[[Timeline of investigations into Trump and Russia (January\u2013June 2018)]]\n*[[Timeline of investigations into Trump and Russia (July\u2013December 2018)]]\n*[[Timeline of investigations into Trump and Russia (2019\u20132020)]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|25em}}\n\n== Sources ==\n{{Bioguide}}\n\n== External links ==\n*{{Commons category-inline}}\n*{{Wikisource author-inline|Jefferson Beauregard Sessions}}\n*{{Wikiquote-inline}}\n* [https://www.justice.gov/ag/bio/attorney-general-jeff-sessions Attorney General bio]\n* {{Curlie|Regional/North_America/United_States/Alabama/Government/Federal/US_Senate/Jeff_Sessions_%5BR%5D}}\n* {{C-SPAN|jeffsessions}}\n{{CongLinks |congbio=s001141 |congress=jeff-sessions/1548}}\n* [http://www.politico.com/news/jeff-sessions Collected news and commentary] from ''[[Politico]]''\n\n{{s-start-collapsible|header={{s-legal}}}}\n{{s-bef|before=William Kimbrough}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[United States Attorney]] for the [[United States District Court for the Southern District of Alabama|Southern District of Alabama]]|years=1981\u20131993}}\n{{s-aft|after=Don Foster}}\n|-\n{{s-bef|before=Jimmy Evans}}\n{{s-ttl|title=